node.text: whether it's for your phone, airpods case, watchbands or water bottle, we have the perfect matching prints for you to #ShowYourColors.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by CASETiFY on August 02, 2021 tagging @casetifybands. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text: wrap that wrist in a Stainless Steel Watchband. ⌚ made from premium stainless steel, it’s lightweight, water and sweat resistant, plus easy to install and adjust. comes in five colors: blue, gold, silver, black, and two-toned gold/silver, you'll want them all.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by CASETiFY on August 01, 2021 tagging @casetifybands. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text: our saffiano leather watchbands come in ~*literally thousands*~ of prints. made out of biodegradable leather and is sweat and water resistant. 💦 it’s time for an upgrade!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by CASETiFY on July 31, 2021 tagging @niasioux. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text: Yippeeecayyyaayyyyyy! 🤠 our photo grid case has DEFENSiFY anti-microbial coating that eliminates 99% of bacteria... so you can ride into the sunset with peace of mind. 📸: @niasioux

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CASETiFY on July 30, 2021. May be an image of saddle-stitched leather, phone, purse and text that says 'CASETIFY Nathan f CASETIFY'.

node.text: we're not playing! 🎮 the switch carry case is designed with 90% recycled materials and 100% recycled packaging, making it the most secure [and sustainable] way to go hands-free. plus, the pouch can hold up to 10 games with functional compartments. we challenge you to customize it and make it your own.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CASETiFY on July 29, 2021. May be an image of bottle and text that says 'THOMAS 3 NATASHA NATASHA'.

node.text: we're on a mission to bring you the best: for your tech and the planet. 🌎 we make conscious decisions by using sustainable materials, eco-friendly ink and 100% recyclable packaging to eliminate as much plastic as possible. join us to make a difference. #DropToZero

node.text:
